solution.p:
The exact solution sets are (according to the choice of the second equation),
                    &x^2+y^2= 4,
                    &\set{
                    \left( \sqrt{\frac{5}{2}}, \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}\right),\,
                    \left(-\sqrt{\frac{5}{2}}, \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}\right),\,
                    \left( \sqrt{\frac{5}{2}},-\sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}\right),\,
                    \left(-\sqrt{\frac{5}{2}},-\sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}\right)
                    }
                    &x^2+2x+y^2=3,\quad\set{(1,0),\,(-2,\sqrt{3}),\,(-2,-\sqrt{3})}
                    &x^2+y^2=1,\quad\set{(1,0),\,(-1,0)}
                    &x^2-4x+y^2=-3,\quad\set{(1,0)}
                    &-x^2+y^2=1,\quad\set{}
